    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-28T04:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-28T04:35:00-05:00" n="421"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d421">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/14473: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-28T13:00:00+03:25"
                            >August 28, 1941—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>116. The British Minister and Russian Ambassador were separately summoned at noon
                    today by the new Foreign Minister<note n="14a" xml:id="d421fn14a">Ali
                        Soheily.</note> and told that the Iranian Government has given orders to
                    cease all opposition and is prepared to meet any terms.</p>
                <p>The two envoys are telegraphing the foregoing to London and Moscow respectively
                    and are requesting instructions.</p>
                <p>The Russian Ambassador has stated that the Russians are making such rapid headway
                    that advanced forces should reach Tehran within the next 24 hours.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
